physics_models.name: Structural Integrity
physics_models.equations: Safety Factor = Ultimate Strength / (Load / Cross-Sectional Area)
physics_models.coding_directives: Calculate safety factor for the framework.
physics_models.python_code:
def calculate_safety_factor(ultimate_strength, load, area):
    return ultimate_strength / (load / area)
physics_models.coder_notes: This model calculates the safety factor for the framework.
assumptions: Load includes weight of components and water.

Lightweight_Framework.verification_plan: Test structural integrity under various loads.
